truth:
Directory layout that exists when the agent starts:

/home/user/db_metrics/query_metrics.json
------------------------------------------------
{
  "queries": [
    {
      "id": "Q123",
      "statement": "SELECT * FROM users;",
      "execution_time_ms": 153
    },
    {
      "id": "Q124",
      "statement": "UPDATE orders SET status='SHIPPED' WHERE id=100;",
      "execution_time_ms": 2345
    },
    {
      "id": "Q125",
      "statement": "DELETE FROM sessions WHERE last_active < NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days';",
      "execution_time_ms": 1820
    },
    {
      "id": "Q126",
      "statement": "SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE amount > 1000;",
      "execution_time_ms": 2890
    }
  ]
}

/home/user/db_metrics/query_metrics_schema.json
------------------------------------------------
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "title": "QueryMetrics",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["queries"],
  "properties": {
    "queries": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["id", "statement", "execution_time_ms"],
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "statement": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "execution_time_ms": {
            "type": "number"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

Expected artefacts the agent must create:

1. /home/user/db_metrics/slow_queries.json  
   Parsed JSON (whitespace is ignored by the grader) must be exactly:
   {
     "slow_queries": [
       {
         "id": "Q124",
         "statement": "UPDATE orders SET status='SHIPPED' WHERE id=100;",
         "execution_time_ms": 2345
       },
       {
         "id": "Q126",
         "statement": "SELECT * FROM transactions WHERE amount > 1000;",
         "execution_time_ms": 2890
       }
     ]
   }

2. /home/user/db_metrics/validation.log  
   Must contain exactly two lines terminated by newlines (Unix line endings):
   Line 1: VALID  
   Line 2: SLOW_IDS:Q124,Q126  

No additional trailing spaces are allowed on either line.

The grader will:
• Confirm that slow_queries.json is valid JSON, has the outer key "slow_queries", and that the array contains exactly the two expected objects in the same order.  
• Read validation.log and check that the first line is the literal word VALID and the second line is the exact literal string "SLOW_IDS:Q124,Q126".  
• Ensure no extra files exist inside /home/user/db_metrics other than the four explicit files:
        query_metrics.json
        query_metrics_schema.json
        slow_queries.json
        validation.log
